cs.MA, cs.CY, cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper proposes an incentive mechanism for crowdsourcing, which involves multiple agents (workers and platform). 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the social welfare and economic properties of the proposed mechanism. 
- cs.GT (Game Theory) is relevant as the paper models the competition between the proposed mechanism and an existing work. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper discusses the interaction among participants in crowdsourcing. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the scalability and efficiency of crowdsourcing in IoT systems.
